Maya Angelou was honored by the US Postal Service on Tuesday for her contributions to the arts . 
  The author of I Know Why the Cage Bird Sings and On the Pulse of Morning was issued a Forever stamp in honor of her achievements . 
  The stamp features a quote attributed to Angelou but was actually written by another author . 
  Joan Walsh Anglund wrote in her 1967 book A Cup of Sun that 'a bird doesn't sing because it has a song' The quote was used on the stamp and in an interview in which Angelou herself used it . 
  The Forever stamp was unveiled at an event with First Lady Michelle Obama and Oprah Winfrey . 
 